blocks.name: dvsubf
blocks.content: The subtraction rule for everywhere-differentiable functions. (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)
blocks.origin:
thm dvsubf(class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3, wff w0) {
  |- wi(w0, wceq(co(c0, cdv, co(c1, cof(cmin), c2)), co(co(c0, cdv, c1), cof(cmin), co(c0, cdv, c2))))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c0, cpr(cr, cc)))
  -| wi(w0, wf(c1, c3, cc))
  -| wi(w0, wf(c2, c3, cc))
  -| wi(w0, wceq(cdm(co(c0, cdv, c1)), c3))
  -| wi(w0, wceq(cdm(co(c0, cdv, c2)), c3))
} = {
  3eqtr4d(co(c0, cdv, co(c1, cof(cmin), c2)), co(co(c0, cdv, c1), cof(cmin), co(c0, cdv, c2)), co(c0, cdv, cmpt(hs0, c3, co(cfv(c1, cv(hs0)), cmin, cfv(c2, cv(hs0))))), cmpt(hs0, c3, co(cfv(co(c0, cdv, c1), cv(hs0)), cmin, cfv(co(c0, cdv, c2), cv(hs0)))), w0)
  dvmptsub(hs0, c0, c3, cfv(c1, cv(hs0)), cfv(c2, cv(hs0)), cfv(co(c0, cdv, c1), cv(hs0)), cfv(co(c0, cdv, c2), cv(hs0)), cc, cc, w0)
  eqtr3d(co(c0, cdv, cmpt(hs0, c3, cfv(c1, cv(hs0)))), cmpt(hs0, c3, cfv(co(c0, cdv, c1), cv(hs0))), co(c0, cdv, c1), w0)
  oveq2d(c0, cdv, c1, cmpt(hs0, c3, cfv(c1, cv(hs0))), w0)
  eqtr3d(co(c0, cdv, cmpt(hs0, c3, cfv(c2, cv(hs0)))), cmpt(hs0, c3, cfv(co(c0, cdv, c2), cv(hs0))), co(c0, cdv, c2), w0)
  oveq2d(c0, cdv, c2, cmpt(hs0, c3, cfv(c2, cv(hs0))), w0)
  oveq2d(c0, cdv, co(c1, cof(cmin), c2), cmpt(hs0, c3, co(cfv(c1, cv(hs0)), cmin, cfv(c2, cv(hs0)))), w0)
  offval2(hs0, c1, cmin, c2, c3, cfv(c1, cv(hs0)), cfv(c2, cv(hs0)), universe, cc, cc, w0)
  ffvelrnda(cv(hs0), c3, c1, cc, w0)
  ffvelrnda(cv(hs0), c3, c2, cc, w0)
  feqmptd(hs0, c1, c3, cc, w0)
  feqmptd(hs0, c2, c3, cc, w0)
  offval2(hs0, co(c0, cdv, c1), cmin, co(c0, cdv, c2), c3, cfv(co(c0, cdv, c1), cv(hs0)), cfv(co(c0, cdv, c2), cv(hs0)), universe, cc, cc, w0)
  syl6eqelr(c3, universe, cdm(co(c0, cdv, c1)), w0)
  dmex(co(c0, cdv, c1))

  ffvelrnda(cv(hs0), c3, co(c0, cdv, c1), cc, w0)

  feqmptd(hs0, co(c0, cdv, c1), c3, cc, w0)
  mpbid(w0, wf(co(c0, cdv, c1), c3, cc), wf(co(c0, cdv, c1), cdm(co(c0, cdv, c1)), cc))
  syl(w0, wf(co(c0, cdv, c1), cdm(co(c0, cdv, c1)), cc), wcel(c0, cpr(cr, cc)))
  dvfg(c0, c1)
  feq2d(co(c0, cdv, c1), cdm(co(c0, cdv, c1)), cc, c3, w0)
  feqmptd(hs0, co(c0, cdv, c2), c3, cc, w0)

blocks.content: A sufficient condition for the derivative of a quotient to be continuous. (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 11-Dec-2019.)
blocks.origin:
thm dvdivcncf(class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3, wff w0) {
  |- wi(w0, wcel(co(c0, cdv, co(c1, cof(cdiv), c2)), co(c3, ccncf, cc)))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c0, cpr(cr, cc)))
  -| wi(w0, wf(c1, c3, cc))
  -| wi(w0, wf(c2, c3, cdif(cc, csn(nat0))))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(co(c0, cdv, c1), co(c3, ccncf, cc)))
